<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-01T17:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-01T17:45:00-05:00" n="750" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.77/249: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-01T17:00:00-05:45">November 1, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>260. In view of the information contained in the Department’s telegram
                            148, October 31, 11 a.m., President Moncada told me this morning that he
                            will proceed on the assumption that the White Corporation will continue
                            its management of the railroad until the end of this year.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>